    <text id="B0329T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>This letter appears to relate to legal services Jackson rendered before his
                    tenure as agent in Staunton.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau of Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands,<lb/>Office Chief Quartermaster
                    and Disbursing Officer, State of Virginia.
                    <name type="recipient">Thos. P. Jackson Esq.<lb/>Agent Bureau <abbr
                            expan="Refugees">R.</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Freedmen">F.</abbr> &amp;c<lb/>Staunton, <abbr
                            expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1867-07-23">July 23d 1867</date>
                        <name type="place">Richmond, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr>,</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir, </salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I have the honor to enclose herewith for your signature to the receipts vouchers
                    in your favor for services rendered as arbitrator of the Taylor Farm in the
                    month of November 1866. Please return them at your earliest convenience.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very Respectfully<lb/>Your Obedient Servant</salute>
                    <signed>Frank A. White<lb/>Chief Clerk</signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">in the absence of Brevet Major Geo. D. White<lb/>Chief
                            <abbr expan="Quarter Master and Disbursing Officer">Qr.Mst. &amp;
                            D.O.</abbr></seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
